tourBios.carHigh:
2015: Recorded first top-10 (T4) of sophomore season on the Mackenzie Tour at the SIGA Dakota Dunes Open with four rounds in the 60s at The Wildfire Invitational...Jump-started Thursday's opening round at the season-ending Freedom 55 Financial Championship with a 63, good for a three-shot lead. Capped Sunday's round with a 64 and earned a solo fourth finish with a 13-under 267...Ended season 29th on the Order of Merit.



2014: Earned conditional status at the 2014 California Qualifying School...In first Mackenzie Tour start, finished T4 at the season-opening PC Financial Open, shooting rounds of 67-67-71-70. Four-day total of 275 was three shy of champion Joel Dahmen...Posted rounds of 67-68 on the weekend to finish T5 at the Staal Foundation Open for second top-10 of the season...Closed with a 7-under-par 65 and a T8 finish at the Cape Breton Open for third top 10.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: In 2012 was an honorable mention All-American and the University of Mexico's Student Athlete of the Year. Won the Arizona Intercollegiate...Earned Mountain West Conference Freshman of the Year honors in 2010.
tourBios.personal: Biggest thrill outside golf is challenging himself in faith...Is involved with the Food for Hungry charity, and he sponsors a child...Brother played college golf at Santa Clara.

dyn.dynResults: He has finished 4th on the Mackenzie Tour-PGA T 3 times.
dyn.dynStats: He ranks T36th in Scoring Average (Actual) on the Mackenzie Tour-PGA TOUR Canada.
